Stacked barplot

Overview of the samples and fractions. It looks like most fractions are missing samples but plasma has the most and buffy coat the second most. RBC and WB are missing quite a few samples and should not be analyzed.

ps_nomc_rel <- ps_nomc %>% 
  transform_sample_counts(., function(x) 100* x/sum(x))

ps_df <- psmelt(ps_nomc_rel)
ps_df <- ps_df %>% 
  filter(dnase == "no")

color_dfs <- create_color_dfs(ps_df, selected_groups = c("Bacteroidota", "Actinobacteriota", "Proteobacteria", "Firmicutes"))


# reorder_samples_by will change the order of samples based on an abundance of a specified subgroup taxonomy
firm_order <- reorder_samples_by(color_dfs$mdf, color_dfs$cdf, order = "Firmicutes", group_level = "Phylum", subgroup_level = "Genus", sink_abundant_groups = FALSE)

firm_legend <-custom_legend(firm_order$mdf, firm_order$cdf, legend_orientation = "horizontal")


stacked_plot <- plot_microshades(firm_order$mdf, firm_order$cdf, x = "patient_ID", group_label = "Phylum-Genus") + 
  xlab("patient_ID") +
  theme(legend.position = "none") +
  facet_grid(fraction~disease, scales = "free") +
  ylab("Relative Abundance")

FigS9 / firm_legend

It’s looking like Proteobacteria is missing from the low-grade and screen-negative samples. I noticed the only proteobacteria present in screen-negative was Legionella, which can be found in humans but is also found in water and soil and could be a contaminant.

ps_nomc_p <- ps %>% 
  tax_glom(., "Phylum", NArm = FALSE) %>% 
  subset_samples(., fraction == "plasma") %>% 
  subset_samples(., dnase == "no")
ps_nomc_p <- subset_taxa(ps_nomc_p, taxa_sums(ps_nomc_p)>0)

ps_nomc_p <- transform_sample_counts(ps_nomc_p, function(x) 100* x/sum(x))

ps_melt <- psmelt(ps_nomc_p)

summary_phylum <- ps_melt %>%
        group_by(Phylum, fraction, patient_ID, disease) %>%
        summarise(Abundance = Abundance, rank_abundance = sum(Abundance), mean_abundance = mean(Abundance), median_abundance = median(Abundance), min_abundance = min(Abundance), max_abundance = max(Abundance)) %>%
        arrange(desc(rank_abundance)) %>%
        mutate(order = row_number())

head(summary_phylum$Phylum)

Firmicutes

summary_phylum$disease <- factor(summary_phylum$disease, levels = c("screen-negative", "low-grade", "high-grade"))


firm_plot <- summary_phylum %>%
  filter(Phylum == "Firmicutes") %>% 
  mutate(disease_plot = case_when(
    disease == "screen-negative" ~ "screen-\nnegative",
    disease == "low-grade" ~ "low-\ngrade",
    disease == "high-grade" ~ "high-\ngrade"
  )) %>% 
  ggplot(., aes(x = disease_plot, y = Abundance)) + 
  geom_boxplot() + 
  geom_beeswarm() +
  theme_bw() +
  xlab("") + 
  theme(legend.position = "none", text = element_text(size = 8)) + 
  ylab("Rel. Abundance (%)") + 
  ggtitle("Firmicutes in Plasma")


stat.test <- psmelt(ps_nomc_p) %>% 
  filter(Phylum == "Firmicutes") %>% 
  wilcox_test(Abundance ~ disease, p.adjust.method = "fdr")
stat.test <- stat.test %>% add_xy_position(x = "disease")

firm <- firm_plot + stat_pvalue_manual(stat.test, label = "p.adj", y.position = c(105, 115, 128), size = 2.5) + scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0.05, 0.15)))

Alpha diversity

Next examining alpha diversity between disease and plasma or BF

meta <- meta %>% 
  mutate(estimate_richness(ps_nomc, measures = c("Observed", "Shannon", "InvSimpson")))

sample_data(ps_nomc) <- meta


meta_ps_long <- melt(meta) %>% filter(variable %in% c("Shannon", "Observed", "InvSimpson"))
## Using patient_ID, fraction, dnase, is.neg, extraction, sam_names, disease as id variables
meta_ps_long$fraction <- factor(meta_ps_long$fraction, levels = c("plasma", "RBC", "BF", "WB"))
meta_ps_long$disease <- factor(meta_ps_long$disease, levels = c("screen-negative", "low-grade", "high-grade"))

FigS8 <- meta_ps_long %>%

Chord Diagrams

Define Functions

create_chord_disease <- function(mdf, column) {
  # create binary presence/absence of connections
    mdf_binary<- mdf %>%
    select(patient_ID, disease, Abundance, Phylum, fraction) %>%
      #mutate(Abundance = if_else(Abundance >1, 1,0)) %>%
    unique()
  
    # count connections between fraction and phyla
    mdf_counts <- mdf_binary %>%
      group_by(disease, Phylum, fraction) %>%  # group them
      summarise(freq = sum(Abundance))  %>%
      unique()

    # count number of samples with each fraction
    sp_counts <- mdf_binary %>%
      select(patient_ID, disease, fraction) %>%
      group_by(disease) %>% unique() %>% # group them
      summarise(count_sp = n())
    
    mdf_counts <- left_join(mdf_counts, sp_counts, by = "disease")
    # calc proportion of co-occurrence for each fraction
    
    mdf_counts <- mdf_counts %>% mutate(prop = freq/count_sp)
    
    # order the data frame
    mdf_counts <- mdf_counts[order(-mdf_counts$prop),]
    

    ## using proportion as the value
    mdf.space <- mdf_counts %>% 
      select(disease, Phylum, {{column}}, prop)
    return(mdf.space)
  }
